# Welcome to Storybook

Storybook is now set up for your AST Boilerplate project!

## What is Storybook?

Storybook is a tool for developing and testing UI components in isolation. It helps you:
- Build components independently from your app
- Test different component states
- Document components with examples
- Share components with your team

## Getting Started

### Running Storybook

Start the Storybook development server:

```bash
pnpm run storybook
```

This will start Storybook on [http://localhost:6006](http://localhost:6006)

### Building Storybook

Build a static version of Storybook:

```bash
pnpm run build-storybook
```

## Creating Stories

Since this project uses Astro components, you'll need to:

1. **Render the HTML structure** - Astro components are compiled to HTML, so in Storybook we recreate that HTML structure
2. **Apply styles** - Import component-specific styles in your story files
3. **Initialize JavaScript** - If your component has interactive behavior, you'll need to initialize it

### Example Story Structure

```javascript
export default {
  title: 'Components/MyComponent',
  tags: ['autodocs'],
};

const Template = (args) => {
  return `
    <div class="my-component">
      {/* Component HTML here */}
    </div>
  `;
};

export const Default = Template.bind({});
Default.args = {
  // Component props/args here
};
```

